    \includegraphics[width=.6\textwidth]{figures/div_free_denoising.pdf}
    \caption{\textbf{Removing the expected divergence of pretrained MMSE denoisers.} Considering the DRUNet as an approximate MMSE denoiser, we use the formula in \cref{eq: divfree from mmse} to evaluate its ZED version and plot the expected theoretical error according to \cref{eq: theoretical DMSE1}. The ZED correction only results in a loss of less than 1 dB for most noise levels. Moreover, the theoretical error follows very closely the empirical one.}
